caption.text:
Pricing strategy I use to make multiple 6 figures a month in sales on Instagram 👇

There are basically three different pricing strategies.

You can sell low-ticket, mid-ticket, and high-ticket offers.

These could include online courses, e-books, community subscriptions, consultations, one-on-one coaching, and high-ticket services like “done-for-you” or “done-with-you” coaching.

How to Decide What to Sell and How Much to Charge:

First, double-check the nature of your service or product. 

Ask yourself if it helps people make or save money. 

For example, my program teaches people how to convert followers into customers, so I help them get more clients and sales directly on Instagram. 

Because of this, I can charge up to 100% of my avatar’s monthly income, especially for one-on-one programs where I offer a very hands-on approach and support.

For less hands-on services, like an online course, you can charge up to 50% of their monthly income. 

For low-ticket offers, something easy to consume with little to no support, you can charge 20% to 30% of their monthly income for a DIY course or e-book.

If your service or product doesn’t directly help people make money but helps with other areas of life like health, relationships etc, for one-on-one programs, you can charge up to 40% of their monthly income. For low-ticket offers, you can charge 5% to 20% of their monthly income.

Save this reel to implement this formula later.

caption.text:
4 tips to turn followers into customers 👇

After working with hundreds of different Instagram accounts over the last 12 months, here’s what we found:

1️⃣ DM me vs. Comment me

The “Comment me” call to action converts views into leads 4 times better than “DM me.”

2️⃣ Visible CTA vs. Not Visible CTA

If you place your call to action in the first line of your caption instead of the last line, you can generate up to 2 times more leads.

3️⃣ Lead Magnet Funnel vs. Buy My Stuff Funnel

If you ask people to reach out to learn more about your products or services, you’ll generate very few leads—around 0.5% of your average Reel views turning into monthly leads.

But if you promote a lead magnet instead of your services, you can get 5% of your average Reel views converting into monthly leads.

4️⃣ Linktree in Bio vs. Lead Form in Bio

You can convert up to 30% of your website taps into leads if you use a lead form in your bio link.

Right now, we’re seeing people using Linktree funnels with multiple links, and they get less than a 5% conversion rate from Instagram website taps into leads.

Do you want me and my team to help you convert followers into customers?

If you’re averaging at least 2,000 Reel views on Instagram, we can scale your business to 5-6 figures.

Comment ➕ to learn more

caption.text:
Follow-ups will 2x your sales 👇

The Manychat funnel is becoming increasingly popular.

Businesses are implementing the “comment me …” strategy and starting to get leads.

However, many businesses then face a common problem: leads don’t respond to the first message.

The key is to follow up with your leads, even if they ignore your first message. More than 90% of your leads will likely ignore it.

Why? People are busy. Some only wanted your free gift. Others intended to respond but forgot. Some think it’s a bot responding, not a real person.

So, the key is to follow up with them in a relaxed, even humorous way, to keep the conversation light, build rapport, and show that it’s really you messaging them, not a bot.

P.S. There will still be a small percentage of people who might get annoyed. But it doesn’t make sense not to double your sales just because 5% of people may be annoyed by follow-ups.

Comment $100k and I’ll dm you my new free 1h training on how to scale your business to $100k in sales on Instagram

I teach you 4 steps to turn followers into more customers
